description:
As a tribute to Robin Williams I've ripped a full-size copy of what many consider to be his best recorded concert - Live at the Met - 1986.

This concert has never been released on DVD AFAIK so any rips around are from TV or VHS. This one is from VHS tape, so accept that the quality will be VHS and not crisp DVD.

I've seen a  few other rips around (on YouTube and Pirate Bay) but they all seem to be low res. This one is full res (720x576) from a PAL VHS.


I have a _very_ slow rural connection so can seed only for a limited time. Be grateful if some other seeders can help out ASAP.
